## HubSpot OAuth Security

- OAuth tokens stored in Convex — never in client state or `localStorage`
- Access tokens encrypted at rest using a server-side key before storage
- Refresh tokens rotated on every use
- OAuth state parameter validated on callback to prevent CSRF
- Scopes requested — minimum required:

```
crm.objects.contacts.read
content
```

- Token refresh logic:

```typescript
async function getValidHubSpotToken(workspaceId: Id<"workspaces">) {
  const connection = await getHubSpotConnection(workspaceId)
  if (isExpired(connection.accessToken)) {
    return await refreshHubSpotToken(connection.refreshToken)
  }
  return connection.accessToken
}
```

